obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32268)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32268&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32269)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to the policy of the State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32269&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that this Act is for giving effect to`
  line `the policy of the State towards securing the principles specified in clause (c) of article 39 of the`
  line Constitution.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section, "State" has the same meaning as in article 12 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32270)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32270&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) acquiring company means any Indian insurance company and, where a scheme has been`
  line `framed involving the merger of one Indian insurance company in another or the amalgamation of two`
  line `or more such companies, means the Indian insurance company in which any other company has been`
  line `merged or the company which has been formed as a result of the amalgamation;`
  line
  line `(b) appointed day means such day not being a day later than the 2nd day of January, 1973, as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) “board of directors” or “board”, in relation to a specified insurer, shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (10) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);]`
  line
  line `(c) Companies Act means ^2[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)];`
  line
  line `(d) Corporation means the General Insurance Corporation of India formed under section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) existing insurer means every insurer the management of whose undertaking has vested in`
  line `the Central Government under section 3 of the General Insurance (Emergency Provisions) Act, 1971`
  line `(17 of 1971), and includes the undertaking of the Life Insurance Corporation in so far as it relates to`
  line `the general insurance business carried on by it;`
  line
  line `(f) foreign insurer means an existing insurer incorporated under the law of any country outside`
  line India;
  line
  line `^3[(g) “general insurance business shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938);]`
  line
  line `(h) Government company means a Government company as defined in ^4[ clause (45) of section 2] of the`
  line `Companies Act;`
  line
  line `(i) Indian insurance company means an existing insurer having a share capital who is a`
  line `company within the meaning of the Companies Act;`
  line
  line `(j) Insurance Act means the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938);`
  line
  line `(k) Life Insurance Corporation means the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under`
  line `the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(l) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(m) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) Schedule means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) scheme means the scheme framed under section 16 ^5[and also includes a scheme framed`
  line `under section 17A;]`
  line
  line `^6[(oa) “specified insurer” means the Corporation as defined in clause (d) or any of the insurance companies specified in section 10A;]`
  line
  line `(p) words and expressions used in this Act but not defined herein and defined in the Insurance`
  line `Act, shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act;`
  line
  line `(q) words and expressions used in this Act but not defined herein or in the Insurance Act and`
  line `defined in the Companies Act, shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the`
  line `Companies Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 37 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (g) (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “section 617” (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1985, s. 2 (w.e.f.17-9-1984).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 37 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32271)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Transfer of shares of Indian insurance companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32271&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed day, all the shares in`
  line `the capital of every Indian insurance company shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to and vested`
  line `in the Central Government free of all trusts, liabilities and encumbrances affecting them.`
  line
  line `(2) Out of the shares so transferred and vested, the Central Government shall, immediately thereafter,`
  line `by notification, provide for the transfer of not less than ten shares of every such company to such persons`
  line `as may be specified in the notification to enable the Indian insurance company to function as a`
  line `Government company.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification made under sub-section (2) shall specify the names and description of the`
  line `persons to whom the shares are transferred and the particulars of the shares which are transferred to each`
  line `such person.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of every notification made under sub-section (2) shall, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `be sent by the Central Government to the concerned Indian insurance company, who shall, on receipt of`
  line `such copy, and notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act or in its articles of association,`
  line `forthwith rectify its register of members by including therein the persons mentioned in the notification as`
  line `the holders of the shares specified therein.`
  line
  line `(5) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that the transfer and vesting of shares effected`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall not be deemed to affect any right of the Indian insurance company subsisting`
  line `immediately before the appointed day against any shareholder to recover from him any sum of money on`
  line `the ground that that shareholder has not paid or credited to the insurer the whole or any part of the value`
  line `of the shares held by him or on any other ground whatsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32272)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Transfer of undertakings of other existing insurers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32272&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed day, the undertaking`
  line `of every existing insurer who is not an Indian insurance company shall stand transferred to and vested in`
  line `the Central Government and the Central Government shall immediately thereafter provide, by`
  line `notification, for the transfer to and vesting in such Indian insurance company, as it may specify in the`
  line `notification, of that undertaking.`
  line
  line `(2) Any notification made under sub-section (1) may provide that any of the undertakings aforesaid`
  line `may be transferred to and vested in more than one Indian insurance company in such manner and subject`
  line `to such conditions as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32273)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Effect of transfer of undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32273&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertaking of every such existing insurer as is`
  line `referred to in section 5 shall be deemed to include all assets, rights, powers, authorities and privileges and`
  line `all property, movable and immovable, cash balances, reserve funds, investments and all other rights and`
  line `interests in, or arising out of, such property as were immediately before the appointed day in the`
  line `ownership, possession, power or control of such existing insurer in relation to the undertaking, whether`
  line `within or without India, and all books of accounts, registers, records and all other documents of whatever`
  line `nature relating thereto, and shall also be deemed to include all borrowings, liabilities and obligations of`
  line `whatever kind then subsisting of the existing insurer in relation to the undertaking.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise expressly provided by this Act, all deeds, bonds, agreements, powers of`
  line `attorney, grants of legal representation and other instruments of whatever nature subsisting or having`
  line `effect immediately before the appointed day and to which any such insurer as is referred to in section 5 is`
  line `a party or which are in favour of such existing insurer shall be of as full force and effect against or in`
  line `favour of the Indian insurance company in which the undertaking or the part to which the instrument`
  line `relates has vested and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectually as if, in the place of the`
  line `existing insurer referred to in section 5, the Indian insurance company in which the undertaking or any`
  line `part thereof has vested had been a party thereto, or as if they had been issued in its favour.`
  line
  line `(3) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature in relation to any`
  line `business of the undertaking which has been transferred under section 5 is pending by or against any such`
  line `existing insurer as is referred to in that section, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be in any way`
  line `prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the undertaking or of anything contained in this Act, but`
  line `the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the Indian`
  line `insurance company in which the undertaking or the part to which the proceeding relates has vested.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that in the case of a foreign insurer or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Life Insurance Corporation, the provisions of section 5 and of the preceding sub-sections`
  line `shall only apply to the extent to which any property appertains, in the former case, to the general`
  line `insurance business carried on in India and, in the latter case, to the general insurance business carried on,`
  line `whether within or without India, and to rights and powers acquired, and to debts, liabilities and`
  line `obligations incurred and to contracts, agreements and other instruments made by the foreign insurer or the`
  line `Life Insurance Corporation, as the case may be, for the purpose of such general insurance business and to`
  line `legal proceedings relating to those purposes, and the said provisions shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) If any question arises as to whether any property appertains to any such general insurance`
  line `business as is referred to in this section or whether any rights, powers, liabilities or obligations were`
  line `acquired or incurred or any contract, agreement or other instrument was made by the foreign insurer or`
  line `the Life Insurance Corporation, as the case may be, for the purposes of any such business or whether any`
  line `documents relate to those purposes, the question shall be referred to the Central Government which shall,`
  line `after giving an opportunity of being heard to the persons interested in the matter, decide it in such manner`
  line `as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32274)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer of service of existing employees in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32274&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every whole-time officer or`
  line `other employee of an existing insurer other than an Indian insurance company who was employed by that`
  line `insurer wholly or mainly in connection with his general insurance business immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall, on the appointed day, become an officer or other employee, as the case may be, of`
  line `the Indian insurance company in which the undertaking of that insurer or that part of the undertaking to`
  line `which the service of the officer or other employee relates has vested, and shall hold his office or service`
  line `under the Indian insurance company on the same terms and conditions and with the same rights to`
  line `pension, gratuity and other matters as would have been admissible to him if there had been no such`
  line `vesting, and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment in the Indian insurance company in`
  line `which the undertaking or part has vested is terminated or until his remuneration, terms and conditions are`
  line `duly altered by that Indian insurance company:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any such officer or other employee who has`
  line `given, in writing, notice to the Central Government or to any person nominated in this behalf by that`
  line `Government before the appointed day intimating his intention of not becoming an officer or employee of`
  line `the Indian insurance company in whom the undertaking or part thereof to which his service relates has`
  line vested.
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any person was a whole-time officer or employee, or as to`
  line `whether any officer or employee, was employed wholly or mainly in connection with the general`
  line `insurance business of the existing insurer referred to in sub-section (1) immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, the question shall be referred within a period of two years from the appointed day and not thereafter`
  line `to the Central Government which shall, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the person`
  line `concerned in the matter, decide it in such manner as it thinks fit and such decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee under sub-section (1) shall not entitle any such officer or other employee to any compensation under that Act or`
  line `such other law, and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32275)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Provident, superannuation, welfare and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32275&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an existing insurer has`
  line `established a provident, superannuation, welfare or any other fund for the benefit of his employees and`
  line `constituted a trust in respect thereof (hereafter in this section referred to as an existing trust), the moneys`
  line `standing to the credit of such fund on the appointed day, together with any other assets belonging to such`
  line `fund, shall stand transferred to and vested in the Indian insurance company on the appointed day free`
  line `from any such trust.`
  line
  line `(2) Where all the employees of the Life Insurance Corporation or any other existing insurer do not`
  line `become employees of an Indian insurance company, the monies and other assets belonging to any such`
  line `fund as is referred to in sub-section (1), shall be apportioned between the trustees of the fund and the`
  line `Indian insurance company in the prescribed manner; and in case of any dispute about such apportionment`
  line `the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the undertaking of an existing insurer has vested in more than one Indian insurance`
  line `company, the Central Government may, by order, provide for the apportionment among such Indian`
  line `insurance companies of monies and other assets belonging to any existing trust relating to that`
  line `undertaking in such manner as in its opinion may be appropriate.`
  line
  line `(4) The Indian insurance company shall as soon as may be after the appointed day constitute in`
  line `respect of the moneys and other assets which are transferred to and vested in it under this section one or`
  line `more trusts having objects as similar to the objects of the existing trusts as in the circumstances may be`
  line practicable.
  line
  line `(5) Where all the moneys and other assets belonging to an existing trust are transferred to and vested`
  line `in an Indian insurance company under this section, the trustees of such trust shall, as from the appointed`
  line `day, stand discharged from the trust, except as respects things done or omitted to be done before the`
  line `appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32276)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Formation of General Insurance Corporation of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32276&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the Central Government shall form a Government company in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of the Companies Act, to be known as the General Insurance Corporation of India for`
  line `the purpose of superintending, controlling and carrying on the business of general insurance:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that on and from the commencement of the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 2002, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words`
  line `superintending, controlling and carrying on the business of general insurance, the words carrying on`
  line `re-insurance business had been substituted.]`
  line
  line `(2) The authorised capital of the Corporation shall be ^2[rupees two hundred and fifty crores, divided`
  line `into two hundred and fifty lakhs fully paid-up shares] of one hundred rupees each, out of which rupees`
  line `five crores shall be the initial subscribed capital of the Corporation:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, increase or reduce the authorised capital`
  line `or subscribed capital, as the case may be, as it deems fit.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in ^3[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)], it shall not be`
  line `necessary to add the word Limited as the last word of the name of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso inserted by Act 40 of 2002, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1989, s. 2, for rupees seventy-five crores, divided into seventy-five lakhs fully paid-up shares`
  line `(w.e.f. 22-10-1989).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 37 of 2021, s. 3, for “the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32277)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Transfer to Corporation of shares vested in Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32277&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `All the shares in the`
  line `capital of every Indian insurance company which stand transferred to and vested in the Central`
  line `Government by virtue of section 4 with the exception of the shares transferred to any person under`
  line `sub-section (2) of that section shall immediately after such vesting, stand transferred to and vested in the Corporation and every Indian insurance company shall forthwith give effect to such transfer of shares and`
  line `rectify its register of members by including therein the Corporation as the holder of such shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (32278)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Transfer to Central Government of shares vested in Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32278&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [10A. Transfer to Central Government of shares vested in Corporation.-- All the shares in the`
  line `capital of the acquiring companies, being--`
  line
  line `(a) the National Insurance Company Limited;`
  line
  line `(b) the New India Assurance Company Limited;`
  line
  line `(c) the Oriental Insurance Company Limited;`
  line
  line `(d) the United India Insurance Company Limited,`
  line
  line `and vested in the Corporation before the commencement of the General Insurance Business`
  line `(Nationalisation) Amendment Act, 2002 shall, on such commencement, stand transferred to the Central`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (32279)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 12
  title `Enhancement of equity capital of General Insurance companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32279&sectionno=10B&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1 [10B. Enhancement of equity capital of General Insurance companies.-- The General Insurance`
  line `Corporation and the insurance companies specified in section 10A may, raise their capital for increasing`
  line `their business in rural and social sectors, to meet solvency margin and such other purposes, as the Central`
  line `Government may empower in this behalf:`
  line
  line ^2*****]
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 5 of 2015, s. 103 (w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 37 of 2021, s. 4 (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32280)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Amounts to be paid for transfer and vesting of shares or undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32280&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the transfer`
  line `of the shares of each Indian insurance company to, and vesting in, the Central Government, under`
  line `section 4, there shall be paid by the Central Government to the Corporation, for distribution to the`
  line `shareholders of each such company, the amount specified against such company in the corresponding`
  line `entry under column (3) of Part A of the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) For the transfer to, and vesting in the Central Government, under section 5, of the undertaking of`
  line `each existing insurer, who is not an Indian insurance company there shall be paid by the Central`
  line `Government to the Corporation, for payment to each such existing insurer, the amount specified against`
  line `such insurer in the corresponding entry under column (3) of Part B of the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32281)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Disbursement of amounts by Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32281&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The total amount paid by the Central`
  line `Government under section 11 shall be treated as additional contribution to the subscribed capital of the`
  line `Corporation and such additional subscribed capital shall stand allotted to, and vested in, the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall distribute the amount paid to it under section 11, to the shareholders of each`
  line `Indian insurance company and to each existing insurer, who is not an Indian insurance company, in`
  line `accordance with their rights and interests, and, if there is any doubt or dispute as to the right, or extent of`
  line `the right, of any person to receive the whole or any part of such amount, refer such doubt or dispute to the`
  line `Central Government for determination and thereafter, act in accordance with the determination made by`
  line `that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), the amount referred to in section 11 shall be given`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of section 13, section 14 or section 15, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32282)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Mode of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32282&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the amount referred to in section 11 is to be given--`
  line
  line `(a) to the members of an Indian insurance company, the amount due to each such member shall`
  line `be paid in full, where it does not exceed twenty-five thousand rupees, and where it exceeds`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees, each such member shall be paid twenty-five thousand rupees and the`
  line `balance of the amount due to such member shall be paid to him in three equal annual instalments, the`
  line `first of which shall fall due on the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(b) to a foreign insurer, it shall be given to him in cash within three months from the appointed`
  line day;
  line
  line `(c) to the Life Insurance Corporation, it shall be given to it in three equal annual instalments, the`
  line `first of which shall fall due on the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(d) to an existing insurer who is a co-operative society, it shall be distributed as soon as may be`
  line `after the appointed day in accordance with the rules of the society which will apply in case of`
  line `dissolution of the society;`
  line
  line `(e) to an existing insurer not falling within any of the foregoing provisions, it shall be apportioned`
  line `by the acquiring company among the individual policy-holders of the insurer whose policies with that`
  line `insurer were in force on the appointed day and were comprised in the undertaking of such insurer in`
  line `proportion to the premiums paid by the policy-holders under such policies and every such payment`
  line `shall be made either--`
  line
  line `(i) in cash, to be sent by postal money order, or`
  line
  line `(ii) at the option of the policy-holder, as a deduction in the premium due at the time of the`
  line `renewal of the policy and such option shall be exercised by the policy-holder before the expiry of`
  line `three months from the appointed day (or within such further time not exceeding three months as`
  line `the Central Government may, on the application of the policy-holder, allow); and the option so`
  line `exercised shall be final and shall not be altered or rescinded after it has been exercised:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any policy-holder fails to exercise his option within the time allowed, he shall be`
  line `deemed to have exercised his option in favour of payment in cash by postal money order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any amount is payable whether in instalments or otherwise under the provisions of this`
  line `section, the unpaid amount, where its payment has become due shall carry interest at the rate of four`
  line `per cent. per annum from the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32283)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Amount payable to shareholders may be paid to named persons instead in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32283&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this Act, if a majority in number of the`
  line `persons, who, immediately before the appointed day, were registered in the books of an Indian insurance`
  line `company as the members thereof, and representing two-thirds in value of the amount payable to the`
  line `Indian insurance company, agree either in person or by proxy at a meeting specially convened for the`
  line `purpose that the amount so payable instead of being distributed among the members shall be given to any`
  line `such person or body of persons as the members may nominate either at that meeting or subsequently for`
  line `the purpose of carrying on any business, and the Central Government is satisfied that due provision has`
  line `been or will be made for the payment of the value of their respective shares to persons who have`
  line `dissented from the reasolution, the amount may be given to the person or body of persons so nominated in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as the Central Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) No resolution passed at any such meeting as is referred to in sub-section (1) held after the`
  line `appointed day shall have any effect unless the meeting has been convened after obtained the approval of`
  line `the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32284)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Payment into court in case of rival claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32284&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where a claim to the amount payable under`
  line `section 11 is made by two or more persons adversely to one another, the corporation may cause the`
  line `amount to be deposited in any civil court having jurisdiction in that behalf and the court shall decide as to`
  line `whom the payment shall be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32285)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Schemes for mergers of companies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32285&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of opinion that for`
  line `the more efficient carrying on of general insurance business it is necessary so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, frame one or more schemes providing for all or any of the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(a) the merger in one Indian insurance company of any other Indian insurance company, or the`
  line `formation of a new company by the amalgamation of two or more Indian insurance companies;`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer to and vesting in the acquiring company of the undertaking (including all its`
  line `business, properties, assets and liabilities) of any Indian insurance company which ceases to exist by`
  line `reason of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) the constitution, name and registered office and the capital structure of the acquiring company`
  line `and the issue and allotment of shares;`
  line
  line `(d) the constitution of a board of management by whatever name called for the management of`
  line `the acquiring company;`
  line
  line `(e) the alteration of the memorandum and articles of association of the acquiring company for`
  line `such purposes as may be necessary to give effect to the scheme;`
  line
  line `(f) the continuance in the acquiring company of the services of all officers and other employees of`
  line `the Indian insurance company which has ceased to exist by reason of the scheme, on the same terms`
  line `and conditions which they were getting or, as the case may be, by which they were governed`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(g) the rationalisation or revision of pay scales and other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `officers and other employees wherever necessary;`
  line
  line `(h) the transfer to the acquiring company of the provident, superannuation, welfare and other`
  line `funds relating to the officers and other employees of the Indian insurance company which has ceased`
  line `to exist by reason of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(i) the continuance by or against the acquiring company of legal proceedings pending by or`
  line `against any Indian insurance company which has ceased to exist by reason of the scheme, and the`
  line `initiation of such legal proceedings, civil or criminal, as the Indian insurance company might have`
  line `initiated if it had not ceased to exist;`
  line
  line `(j) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as are necessary to give full effect to`
  line `the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) In framing schemes under sub-section (1), the object of the Central Government shall be to ensure`
  line `that ultimately there are ^1[up to four companies] (excluding the Corporation) in existing and that they are`
  line `so situate as to render their combined services effective in all parts of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a scheme under sub-section (1) provides for the transfer of any property or liabilities, then,`
  line `by virtue of the scheme, the property shall stand transferred to and vested in, and those liabilities shall be`
  line `transferred to and become the liabilities of, the acquiring company.`
  line
  line `(4) If the rationalisation or revision of any pay scale or other terms and conditions of service under`
  line `any scheme is not acceptable to any officer or other employee, the acquiring company may terminate his`
  line `employment by giving him compensation equivalent to three months' remuneration, unless the contract of`
  line `service with such employee provides for a shorter notice of termination.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The compensation payable to an officer or other employee under this sub-section shall`
  line `be in addition to, and shall not affect, any pension, gratuity, provident fund or other benefit to which the`
  line `employee may be entitled under his contract of service.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee of an`
  line `Indian insurance company to the acquiring company shall not entitled any such officer or other employee`
  line `to any compensation under that Act or other law, and no such claim shall be entertained by any court,`
  line `tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, by notification, add to, amend or vary any scheme framed under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of this section and of any scheme framed under it shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in any other law or any agreement, award or other instrument for the`
  line `time being in force.`
  line
  line `^2[(8) The power to frame a scheme under sub-section (1), and the power conferred by sub-section (6)`
  line `to add to, amend or vary any scheme framed under this section, shall include the power to frame such`
  line `scheme with retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the appointed day.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 149, for the words "only four companies" (w.e.f. 1-8-2019.)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-9-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32286)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Laying of schemes and notifications before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for section 17 (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32286&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1 [17. Laying of schemes and notifications before Parliament.-- Every scheme framed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16 and every notification issued under sub-section (3) of that section shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is framed or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the scheme or notification or both`
  line `Houses agree that the scheme or notification should not be framed or issued, the scheme or notification`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that scheme or notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (32287)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Central Government to regulate the terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1985, s. 4 (w.e.f. 17-9-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32287&sectionno=17A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Power of Central Government to regulate the terms and conditions of service of officers`
  line `and other employees.-- (1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, frame`
  line `one or more schemes for regulating the pay scales and other terms and conditions of service of officers`
  line `and other employees of the Corporation or of any acquiring company.`
  line
  line `(2) A scheme framed under sub-section (1) may add to, amend or vary any scheme framed under`
  line `section 16 [including any addition, amendment or variation made therein by notification under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 16] with respect to rationalisation or revision of pay scales and other terms and`
  line `conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Corporation or of any acquiring company, to`
  line `provide for further rationalisation or revision of such pay scales and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `notwithstanding that such further rationalisation or revision is unrelated to, or unconnected with, the`
  line `amalgamation of insurance companies or merger consequent on nationalisation of general insurance`
  line business.
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, add to, amend or vary any scheme framed under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(4) The power to frame a scheme under sub-section (1), and the power conferred by sub-section (3) to`
  line `add to, amend or vary any scheme framed under this section, shall include the power to frame such`
  line `scheme, or, as the case may be, to make such addition, amendment or variation in any scheme framed`
  line `under this section, with retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(5) A copy of every scheme, and every amendment thereto, framed under this section shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section and of any scheme framed under it shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in any other law or any agreement, award or other instrument for the`
  line `time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32288)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Functions of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32288&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of the Corporation shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) the carrying on of any part of the general insurance business, if it thinks it desirable to do so;`
  line
  line `(b) aiding, assisting and advising the acquiring companies in the matter of setting up of standards`
  line `of conduct and sound practice in general insurance business and in the matter of rendering efficient`
  line `service to holders of policies of general insurance;`
  line
  line `(c) advising the acquiring companies in the matter of controlling their expenses including the`
  line `payment of commission and other expenses;`
  line
  line `(d) advising the acquiring companies in the matter of the investment of their funds;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing directions to acquiring companies in relation to the conduct of general insurance`
  line `business:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that all the functions of the Corporation specified in this sub-section, on and from the`
  line `commencement of the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Amendment Act, 2002, shall be`
  line `performed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) In issuing any directions under sub-section (1), the ^2[Central Government] shall keep in mind the`
  line `desirability of encouraging competition amongst the acquiring companies as far as possible in order to`
  line `render their services more efficient.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32289)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Functions of acquiring companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32289&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the rules, if any, made by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf and to its memorandum and articles of association, it shall be the duty of every`
  line `acquiring company to carry on general insurance business.`
  line
  line `(2) Each acquiring company shall so function under this Act as to secure that general insurance`
  line `business is developed to the best advantage of the community.`
  line
  line `(3) In the discharge of any of its functions, each acquiring company shall act so far as may be on`
  line `business principles and where any directions have been issued by the ^1[`
  line `Central Government or the`
  line `Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the`
  line `Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999] (41 of 1999), shall be guided by such`
  line directions.
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that the Corporation and any acquiring company`
  line `may, subject to the rules, if any, made by the Central Government in this behalf, enter into such contracts`
  line `of reinsurance or reinsurance treaties as it may think fit for the protection of its interests.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32290)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Balance of profit how to be utilised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32290&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) After making provision for bad and doubtful debts,`
  line `depreciation in assets, provident, superannuation, welfare and other funds, debts due to Government and`
  line `all other matters for which provision is necessary under any law or which are usually provided for by`
  line `insurance companies, every acquiring company shall distribute the balance of profit as dividends.`
  line
  line `(2) Any profit made by the Corporation and any sums received by the Corporation by way of`
  line `dividends or otherwise shall be dealt with by it in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32291)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Interim provisions for management of Indian insurance companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32291&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Companies Act or in the memorandum and articles of association of any Indian`
  line `insurance company, on and from the appointed day and until a new board of directors of the Indian`
  line `insurance company is duly constituted, the management of the company shall continue to vest in the`
  line `Custodian in charge of the management of the undertaking of that company immediately before the`
  line `appointed day by virtue of the provisions contained in the General Insurance (Emergency Provisions) Act,`
  line `1971 (17 of 1971), and the Custodian shall be entitled, subject to such directions as the Central`
  line `Government may issue in this behalf, to exercise all the powers and do all acts and things as may be`
  line `exercised or done by the company or by its board of directors.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to prevent the Central Government from`
  line `appointing any other person to take charge of the management of the undertaking of any Indian insurance`
  line `company during the period referred to in that sub-section if for any reason it becomes necessary so to do,`
  line `and any person so appointed may exercise all the powers and do all acts and things which a Custodian`
  line `may exercise or do under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian referred to in sub-section (1) and the person appointed under sub-section (2) shall`
  line `be entitled to such salaries and other allowances as the Central Government may specify in this behalf and`
  line `shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32292)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Central Government to transfer employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 2002, s. 6, for "The Corporation may at any time transfer any officer" (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32292&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Central Government or any`
  line `person authorised by it may at any time transfer any officer] or employee from an acquiring company or`
  line `the Corporation to any other acquiring company or the Corporation, as the case may be, and the officer or`
  line `employee so transferred, shall continue to have the same terms and conditions of service as were`
  line `applicable to him immediately before such transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32293)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32293&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation and every acquiring`
  line `company shall, in the discharge of its functions, be guided by such directions in regard to matters of`
  line `policy involving public interest as the Central Government may give.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32294)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Acquiring companies to have the exclusive privilege of carrying on general insurance business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32294&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except to the extent expressly provided in this Act, on and from the appointed day, the`
  line `Corporation and the acquiring companies shall have the exclusive privilege of carrying on general`
  line `insurance business in India.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 36, any certificate of registration granted under the Insurance`
  line `Act to any insurer other than an insurer referred to in sub-section (1) shall, on and from the appointed day,`
  line `cease to have effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the carrying on by the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation of life insurance business and capital redemption and annuity certain business.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (32295)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 28
  title `Exclusive privilege of Corporation and acquiring companies to cease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32295&sectionno=24A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Exclusive privilege of Corporation and acquiring companies to cease.-- Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the exclusive privilege of the Corporation and the acquiring companies of`
  line `carrying on general insurance business in India shall cease on and from the commencement of the`
  line `Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 and the Corporation and the acquiring`
  line `companies shall, thereafter, carry on general insurance business in India in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938):`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Corporation shall, on and from the commencement of the General Insurance`
  line `Business (Nationalisation) Amendment Act, 2002, cease to carry on general insurance business].]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 32 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 40 of 2002, s. 7 (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_b:
  sectionId (57911)
  sectionNo 24B
  orderNo 29
  title `Cessation of application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by Act 37 of 2021, s. 5 (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=57911&sectionno=24B&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[24B. Cessation of application of Act.--(1) On and from the date on which the Central Government ceases to control any specified insurer, after the commencement of the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Amendment Act, 2021, the provisions of this Act shall cease to apply in respect of that specified insurer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), on the date of cessation of applicability referred to in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) any scheme framed by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 17A in respect of the specified insurer referred to in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have been adopted by the board of directors of such specified insurer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the board of directors may make such additions, amendments or variations thereto, or frame new policy in place of such scheme, as it may deem appropriate;`
  line
  line `(b) without prejudice to the generality of the power of the board of directors of the specified insurer under clause (a), all powers exercisable by the Central Government under a scheme framed by it in sub-section (1) of section 17A shall be exercisable by that board of directors.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this section, the expression control means the right of the Central Government, in relation to a specified insurer,`
  line
  line `(i) to appoint a majority of its directors; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to have power over its management or policy decisions,`
  line
  line `by virtue of its shareholding rights or management rights under its articles of association or shareholders agreements or voting agreements or any other agreements executed with the specified insurer or any other person in relation to the specified insurer.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that--`
  line
  line `(i) the provisions of this section shall also apply to any rule, scheme, direction or notification made under this Act before the cessation of applicability;`
  line
  line `(ii) the cessation of applicability shall not revive anything that was not already in force or in existence under this Act or affect anything previously done or suffered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) the board of directors of the specified insurer shall exercise the powers referred to in sub-section (2), subject to any requirement under any law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32296)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32296&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `[Properties in India not to be insured with foreign insurers except with permission of Central`
  line `Government.] Omitted by the Insurance Laws (Amendment) Act, 2015 (5 of 2015), s. 104`
  line `(w.e.f. 26-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32310)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 31
  title `Acquiring companies and income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32310&sectionno=26&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961), every acquiring company shall be deemed to be an Indian company and a company in which`
  line `the public are substantially interested.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32311)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to reduce amounts of insurance in certain eases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32311&sectionno=27&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `An acquiring company may, having`
  line `regard to its financial condition on the 13th day of May, 1971 or the financial condition on the said date`
  line `of any existing insurer whose undertaking has been transferred to and vested in it under this Act reduce`
  line `the liabilities which have arisen under contracts of general insurance entered into before the said date in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such reduction shall be made except in accordance with specific proposals made by`
  line `the acquiring company in this behalf and approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32312)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 33
  title `Right of acquiring company to seek relief in respect of certain transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32312&sectionno=28&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an`
  line `existing insurer has at any time within five years before the 13th day of May, 1971--`
  line
  line `(a) made any payment to any person without consideration,`
  line
  line `(b) sold or disposed of any property of the insurer without consideration or for an inadequate`
  line consideration,
  line
  line `(c) acquired any property or rights for an excessive consideration,`
  line
  line `(d) entered into or varied any agreement so as to require an excessive consideration to be paid or`
  line `given by the insurer,`
  line
  line `(e) entered into any other transaction of such an onerous nature as to cause a loss to, or impose a`
  line `liability on, the insurer exceeding any benefit accruing to the insurer,`
  line
  line `and the payment, sale, disposal, acquisition, agreement or variation thereof or other transaction was not`
  line `reasonably necessary for the purpose of the general insurance business of the insurer or was made with an`
  line `unreasonable lack of prudence on the part of the insurer, regard being had in either case to the`
  line `circumstances at the time, the acquiring company may apply for relief to the court in respect of such`
  line `transaction, and all parties to the transaction shall, unless the court otherwise directs, be made parties to`
  line `the application.`
  line
  line `(2) The court may make such order against any of the parties to the application as it thinks just having`
  line `regard to the extent to which those parties were respectively responsible for the transaction or benefited`
  line `from it and all the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made to the court under this section in respect of any transaction and the`
  line `application is determined in favour of the acquiring company, the court shall have exclusive jurisdiction`
  line `to determine any claim outstanding in respect of the transaction.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32313)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 34
  title `Duty to deliver possession of property and documents relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32313&sectionno=29&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `property appertaining to an existing insurer has been transferred to and vested in an Indian insurance`
  line `company under section 5,--`
  line
  line `(a) every person in whose possession, custody or control any such property may be, shall deliver`
  line `the property to the Indian insurance company forthwith,`
  line
  line `(b) any person who immediately before such vesting has in his possession, custody or control any`
  line `books, documents or other papers relating to an existing insurer shall be liable to account for the said`
  line `books, documents and papers to the Indian insurance company, and shall deliver them to that`
  line `company or to such person as that company may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, all the assets of an existing insurer appertaining to the undertaking held in deposit by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India under the Insurance Act or by trustees in trust shall be delivered to the Indian`
  line `insurance company.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the other provisions contained in this section, it shall be lawful for each`
  line `Indian Insurance company to take all necessary steps for taking possession of all properties which have`
  line `been transferred to and vested in it under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32314)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 35
  title `Penalty for withholding property, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32314&sectionno=30&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If any person wilfully withholds or fails to deliver to an`
  line `Indian insurance company as required by section 29 any property or any books, documents or other`
  line `papers which may be in his possession or unlawfully retains possession of any property of an existing`
  line `insurer which has been transferred to and vested in an Indian insurance company under section 5 or`
  line `wilfully applies any such property to purposes other than those expressed in or authorised by this Act, he`
  line `shall, on the complaint of the Indian insurance company, be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32315)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 36
  title `Officers and employees of Corporation or of acquiring companies to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32315&sectionno=31&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every officer or other employee of the Corporation or of an acquiring company shall be`
  line `deemed to be a public servant for the purposes of Chapter IX of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (57912)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 37
  title `Liability of director of specified insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 37 of 2021, s. 6 (w.e.f. 27-8-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=57912&sectionno=31A&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Liability of director of specified insurer.--A director of a specified insurer who is not its whole-time director shall be held liable only in respect of such acts of omission or commission of the specified insurer which had been committed with his knowledge, attributable through board processes, and with his consent or connivance or where he had not acted diligently.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the reference to board shall include committees of the board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32316)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 38
  title Indemnity
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32316&sectionno=32&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every officer of the Central Government and every officer or other employee of the`
  line `Corporation and of any acquiring company shall be indemnified by the Central Government or the`
  line `Corporation or the acquiring company, as the case may be, against all losses and expenses incurred by`
  line `him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his duties under this Act except such as have been caused by his`
  line `own wilful act or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32317)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 39
  title `Dissolution of Corporation and acquiring companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32317&sectionno=33&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the`
  line `winding up of companies shall apply to the Corporation or to an acquiring company, and neither the Corporation nor any such company shall be placed in liquidation save by order of the Central Government`
  line `and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32318)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 40
  title `Reference to existing insurer in other laws`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32318&sectionno=34&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any reference to an existing insurer in any law`
  line `other than this Act or any contract or other instrument shall, in so far as it relates to an acquiring`
  line `company, be construed as a reference to that company.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32319)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 41
  title `Application of Insurance Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32319&sectionno=35&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such exceptions, restrictions and limitations, if any,`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf, the Insurance Act shall apply to or`
  line `in relation to the Corporation and every acquiring company as if the Corporation or the acquiring`
  line `company, as the case may be, were an insurer carrying on general insurance business within the meaning`
  line `of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35_a:
  sectionId (32320)
  sectionNo 35A
  orderNo 42
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32320&sectionno=35A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content:
  string
  line `[Deduction of income-tax not to be made on interest or dividend payable to the Corporation,`
  line `etc.] Omitted by The Finance Act 2002 (20 of 2002), s. 158 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32321)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 43
  title Exemptions
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32321&sectionno=36&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing contained in this Act shall apply in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) any general insurance business carried on by a State Government, to the extent to which such`
  line `insurance relates to properties belonging to it or undertakings owned wholly or mainly by the State`
  line `Government or to properties belonging to semi-government bodies, or any Board or body corporate`
  line `established by the State Government under any statue or any industrial or commercial undertaking in`
  line `which the State Government has substantial financial interest, whether as shareholder, lender or`
  line guarantor;
  line
  line `(b) any general insurance business not falling within clause (a) which has been carried on by a`
  line `State Government before the commencement of this Act, to the extent to which it is necessary to`
  line `allow such business to run off:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall be deemed to authorise the State Government`
  line `to issue any new policies or renew any existing policies;`
  line
  line `(c) any insurer whose business is being voluntarily wound up or is being wound up by a court;`
  line
  line `(d) the insurance business carried on by the Calcutta Hospital and Nursing Home Benefits`
  line `Association Limited;`
  line
  line `(e) the insurance business carried on by the Export Credit and Guarantee Corporation Limited and`
  line `the Deposit Insurance Corporation established under section 3 of the Deposit Insurance Corporation`
  line `Act, 1961 (47 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(f) any scheme in existence immediately before the 14th day of May, 1971 or any scheme framed`
  line `after the said day with the approval of the Central Government for the insurance of crops or of cattle`
  line `or of flood risks or of war or emergency risks.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government is satisfied that an insurer, whether established before or after the`
  line `appointed day, carries on only such general insurance business as is not carried on ordinarily by insurers,`
  line `it may, by notification, direct that nothing contained in this Act shall apply to such insurer.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32322)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 44
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32322&sectionno=37&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Corporation or of`
  line `an acquiring company shall be called in question merely on the ground of the existence of any vacancy in,`
  line `or defect in the constitution of, the Corporation or the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32323)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 45
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32323&sectionno=38&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any officer of the Central Government or officer or other employee of the Corporation or of the`
  line `acquiring company for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (50608)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 46
  title `Powers of Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 2019, s. 33 and the second Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=50608&sectionno=38A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Powers of Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India not to apply to`
  line `International Financial Services Centre.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, the powers exercisable by the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of`
  line `India under this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) shall not extend to an International Financial Services Centre set up under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be exercisable by the International Financial Services Centres Authority established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4 of the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act, 2019, in so far as regulation of financial products, financial services and financial institutions that are permitted`
  line `in the International Financial Services Centres are concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32324)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 2002, s. 8, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 21-3-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710&sectionId=32324&sectionno=39&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00039_197257_1517807324710
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under this`
  line `section may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the profits, if any, and other moneys received by the Corporation may be`
  line `dealt with;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) the conditions, if any, subject to which the Corporation shall carry on re-insurance business;`
  line
  line `(ba) the conditions, if any, subject to which the acquiring companies shall carry on general`
  line `insurance business;]`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions subject to which any reinsurance contracts or treaties may be entered`
  line into;
  line
  line `(d) the form and manner in which any notice or application may be given or made to the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(e) the reports which may be called for by the Central Government from the Corporation and the`
  line `acquiring companies;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section and every notification issued under section 35 shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or both Houses agree that the`
  line `rule or notification should not be made, the rule or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line notification.
